<p>Suppose I want to create a vector length of 10000 with random numbers of 1-4 of equal counts (also each number appears exact once in every 4 numbers with different ordering). I can use the following R code with a <code>for()</code> loop:</p>  <pre><code>res &lt;- NULL for (i in 1:10000) {    set.seed(i)    res &lt;- c(res, sample(1:4)) } </code></pre>  <p>And I got</p>  <pre><code>head(res, 20) # [1] 2 4 3 1 1 3 2 4 1 3 4 2 3 1 4 2 1 3 2 4 </code></pre>  <p>Since the <code>for()</code> loop is generally not recommended in R, is there a fast way to achieve this? </p>